            <td class="CONTENTTD" style="font-size: 10px; color: #000000; border: 0px solid;"><a href="http://www.expertretail.com/1/default.asp" style="font-weight: bold;"></a>&nbsp;ERS today announced the appointment of Trade Link Retail Systems (Pty)Ltd as their strategic partner and Master Franchise holder for the African Continent.&nbsp;<br />
            <br />
            "I am delighted that this appointment has been made. This is an important milestone in our 20 year history and re-enforces ERS's commitment to the continued development of our products and support of our customers," Lance Wallis, ERS's CEO commented on the announcement.&nbsp;<br />
            <br />
            "Guided by our Product Development Director, Paul Gwynne, Trade Link Retail Systems will be responsible for the continued development and support of our products. Trade Link have secured additional personal to take on this task. One of the most compelling reasons in deciding to appoint Trade Link as our partner has been our successful relationship with them over the past six years installing Retail solutions in Zimbabwe and South Africa. The two Companies software solutions have complimented each other and this now gives us the opportunity of providing a more unified product portfolio and support infrastructure to service our growing number of clients." Wallis said.&nbsp;<br />
            <br />
            At the same time, it was announced that Expert Retail Systems (Pty) Australia had been established to focus on supplying support and RetailManager to customers in the Pacific Rim and Australian markets.<br />
            <br />
            Further announcements from Tradelink Retail Systems and ERS are expected to be made regarding this appointment and development.</td>
